<subSubSection pageId="60" pageNumber="61" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1437,1289,1569]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1361,1387]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Distribution.</emphasis>
Transeurasiatic, temperate. From European part of 
<collectingCountry box="[934,1009,1362,1388]" name="Russia" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Russia</collectingCountry>
to Primorye, 
<collectingRegion box="[1164,1262,1362,1388]" country="Russia" name="Sakhalin" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Sakhalin</collectingRegion>
Isl. and Kurils. Outside 
<collectingCountry box="[248,323,1398,1424]" name="Russia" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Russia</collectingCountry>
in Europe (
<collectingCountry box="[462,552,1398,1424]" name="Finland" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Finland</collectingCountry>
, Baltic states, 
<collectingCountry box="[721,809,1398,1424]" name="Belarus" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Belarus</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[823,904,1398,1424]" name="Poland" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Poland</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[918,1019,1398,1424]" name="Slovakia" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Slovakia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1031,1118,1398,1425]" name="Austria" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Austria</collectingCountry>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[1139,1203,1398,1424]" name="Japan" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Japan</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[1220,1335,1398,1424]" country="Japan" name="Hokkaido" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Hokkaido</collectingRegion>
, Honshu isl.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1437,1289,1569]" box="[199,599,1470,1497]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
